@startuml
title Design Intake To Roadmap Automation - User Gates And Codex Automation

|User|
start
:Describe new design,
idea, concern, or change request;

|Codex Coordinator|
:Inspect AGENTS, AI_GUIDE,
architecture docs, roadmap docs,
and current code truth;
:Run architecture-governance
workflow kickoff;
:Identify DDD owner,
Clean Architecture direction,
ADR need, ATAM-lite tradeoffs,
Strangler migration shape,
fitness functions, and ownership mode;

if (Intent or product tradeoff unclear?) then (yes)
  |User|
  :Answer targeted clarification
  or choose tradeoff;
  |Codex Coordinator|
  :Update governance recommendation;
else (no)
endif

if (Accepted owner and path exist?) then (yes)
  |Codex Coordinator|
  :Add or update design,
  ADR, or owning roadmap;
  :Assign value, blocker,
  dependency level, gate,
  and next evidence;
  :Update decision register,
  triage, and PUML roadmap
  if topology changes;
else (no)
  :Keep as discovery,
  proposed design, or B5 gate;
  :Record missing owner,
  evidence, ADR, or contract;
endif

|User|
:Review proposed placement
and promotion level;

if (Approve promotion?) then (yes)
  |Codex Coordinator|
  :Make docs/register/diagram
  updates;
  :Run docs validation;
  :Recommend whether it can enter
  the next parallel batch;
  stop
else (no)
  |Codex Coordinator|
  :Leave design gated
  or revise proposal;
  stop
endif

legend right
  <b>User responsibilities</b>
  - Bring an idea, design, or change request
  - Clarify product intent when needed
  - Approve promotion into implementation planning

  <b>Codex automation</b>
  - Investigate repo truth
  - Run architecture governance review
  - Draft or update docs/register/diagram
  - Keep unaccepted work gated
endlegend

@enduml
